topic: Movie Workflow Series ("Film Genre and composer explorative search")

goals.3: Identify the BGP for film genre
goals.4: Find how many films are been released in the United States of America from 2010-01-01 to 2015-31-12 for each film genre available (the result set must be genre IRI, label and #films).
goals.5: Consider the timespan from 2001-01-01 to nowadays. Find the number of films released in this timespan divided by film genre and return only those with more than 50 films released every year (the result set must be genre IRI and label).
goals.6: Consider the composers of Western films and their country of citizenship. Count the number of Western Films on which worked a composer grouped by country of citizenship and return the top-10 (the result set must be country IRI, label and #films)..
goals.7: Consider the decades from 1961 to 1970, and from 2001 to 2010 and compare the total number of western films released in each one (the result set must be two couples decade and #western films of that decade).
goals.8: Consider the decades from 1961 to 1970, and from 2001 to 2010 and select only western films. Then, for each decade, compare the average cast members size per film (the result set must be two couples decade and average cast members size of that decade).

4.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 3 in the file
find the date and the country
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; ?prop ?obj. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"date") || REGEX(?name,"ountr") ). }

4.narrative: use the property publication date and country of origin. But first need to find United States
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P495 ?obj. ?obj sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"[U,u]")). } ORDER BY DESC (?name) LIMIT 20
output: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland

4.narrative: use the property publication date and country of origin. USA (Q30)
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?genre ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?counts WHERE { ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P495 wd:Q30; wdt:P136 ?genre; wdt:P577 ?date. ?genre wdt:P31 wd:Q201658. FILTER ( isLiteral(?date) ) . FILTER(?date>=xsd:date("2010-01-01") && ?date<xsd:date("2016-01-01")). ?genre sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?genre ?name ORDER BY DESC (?counts) LIMIT 10

4.narrative: use the property publication date and country of origin. USA (Q30)
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?genre ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?counts WHERE { ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P495 wd:Q30; wdt:P136 ?genre; wdt:P577 ?date. ?genre wdt:P31 wd:Q201658. FILTER ( isLiteral(?date) ) . FILTER(?date>=xsd:date("1960-01-01") && ?date<xsd:date("1965-01-01")). ?genre sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?genre ?name ORDER BY DESC (?counts) LIMIT 10

5.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
look at the year
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT(YEAR(?date)) AS ?max_year WHERE { ?film wdt:P577 ?date ; wdt:P136 ?genre . ?genre wdt:P31 wd:Q201658 . FILTER(isLiteral(?date)). FILTER(?date >="2018-01-01T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime) }

5.narrative:
find all the genres from 2001 to now that have more than 50 films for each year
we consider films publicated up to 2021 given that the instance of Wikidata is from 2021
5.query: SELECT ?genre ?g_name WHERE{ { SELECT DISTINCT ?genre YEAR(?date) AS ?year (COUNT(?film) AS ?films) WHERE { ?film wdt:P577 ?date ; wdt:P136 ?genre . ?genre wdt:P31 wd:Q201658 . FILTER(?date >="2001-01-01T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime && ?date <="2022-01-01T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime) } GROUP BY ?genre YEAR(?date) } ?genre sc:name ?g_name . FILTER (?films > 50) } GROUP BY ?genre ?g_name HAVING (COUNT(DISTINCT ?year) >20)

6.narrative: find top-10 composers of western films
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?counts WHERE { ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P86 ?composer; wdt:P136 wd:Q172980. ?composer wdt:P27 ?country. ?country sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?country ?name ORDER BY DESC (?counts) LIMIT 10

7.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
compare the decades
7.query: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?counts WHERE { ?film wdt:P136 wd:Q172980 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P577 ?date. FILTER(?date>=xsd:date("1961-01-01") && ?date<xsd:date("1971-01-01")). }
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?counts WHERE { ?film wdt:P136 wd:Q172980 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P577 ?date. FILTER(?date>=xsd:date("2001-01-01") && ?date<xsd:date("2011-01-01")). }

SELECT DISTINCT ?decade (COUNT( DISTINCT ?film) AS ?films) WHERE { ?film wdt:P136 wd:Q172980 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q11424 ; wdt:P577 ?date . FILTER((YEAR(?date) > 1960 && YEAR(?date) <= 1970) || (YEAR(?date) > 2000 && YEAR(?date) <= 2010)) BIND (if(YEAR(?date) > 1960 && YEAR(?date) <= 1970,"1961-1970", "2001-2010") AS ?decade) } GROUP BY ?decade LIMIT 100

8.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
find average cast members size for western films between 1961-1970 and 2001-2010
8.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?decade (AVG(?cast_size) AS ?avg_cast) WHERE { { SELECT DISTINCT ?decade ?film (COUNT(?cast) AS ?cast_size) WHERE { ?film wdt:P136 wd:Q172980 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q11424 ; wdt:P577 ?date ; wdt:P161 ?cast . FILTER((YEAR(?date) > 1960 && YEAR(?date) <= 1970) || (YEAR(?date) > 2000 && YEAR(?date) <= 2010)) BIND (if(YEAR(?date) > 1960 && YEAR(?date) <= 1970,"1961-1970","2001-2010") AS ?decade) } } } GROUP BY ?decade LIMIT 100
